               (Comedy club)

               
               It's tough to do a good deed. Just look at your professional 
               good deed doers. Your lone rangers, your superman, your Batman, 
               your Spiderman, your Elasticman. They are all wearing disguises, 
               masks over their faces. Secret identities. Don't want people 
               to know who they are. It's too much aggravation. "Superman, thanks 
               for saving my life, but did you have to come through my wall? 
               I'm renting here, I've got a security deposit. What am I supposed 
               to do?"
 
               
               
                                THE END

                              THE DOG



                             Written by

                            Larry David




 
               
               
               (Comedy club)

               
               So I'm on the plane, we left late. Pilot says we're going to 
               be making up some
 
               time in the air. I thought, well isn't that interesting. We'll 
               just make up
 
               time. That's why you have to reset your watch when you land. 
               Of course, when
 
               they say they're making up time, obviously they're increasing 
               the speed of the
 
               aircraft. Now, my question is if you can go faster, why don't 
               you just go as
 
               fast as you can all the time? C'mon, there's no cops up here, 
               nail it. Give it
 
               some gas! We're flying!

               
               New scene. Jerry is on an airplane, seated beside a talkative 
               (and inebriated)
 
               man.

               
